# Publish pipeline rules

## Data flow (do not invert)

```
HF dataset → SuperWhisper → harvest → markdown → [memo Apple Notes] → [gog Drive]
```

- Apple Notes / NoteStore watch **triggers sync only**; it does not ingest note bodies.
- macOS Voice Memos is **not** a source.
- `publish.drive_*` (upload) is separate from `watch.drive_*` (sync wake).

## Config gates

| Goal | Required |
|------|----------|
| Any harvest/publish | `publish.enabled = true` |
| Apple Notes | `memo_enabled` + working `memo` / Automation |
| Drive upload | `drive_enabled` + non-empty `drive_folder_id` + `gog` auth (+ prefer `gog_account`) |
| NoteStore wake | `watch.apple_notes_enabled` + Full Disk Access for the **service** binary |

## Failure semantics to preserve / harden

- `MarkPublished` only after all enabled sinks succeed.
- Drive/memo failure must not silently look like success; avoid unbounded `syncMu` hangs (timeouts).
- Daemon sync must not skip harvest/publish backlog when only HF `VerifyAccess` fails — `lazy-notes publish` is the backlog path.
- Doctor PATH/`Stat` greens are not e2e proof; prove with disk note + Notes folder (+ Drive if enabled).

## Solmigo verification before claiming publish works

```bash
lazy-notes doctor
lazy-notes status
lazy-notes publish   # or sync when new HF clips exist
ls -lt ~/.local/share/lazy-notes/notes | head
# Apple Notes folder publish.memo_folder (default Lazy Notes)
```
